The '''Seroglazov culture''' (sometimes erroneously translated as ''Seroglazovka'', or ''Seroglasovo'' culture) is a [[mesolithic]] culture. Pernitzka dated it according to 14C-dating to the beginning of the 7th millennium BC, others (who?) to the [[11th millennium BC|11th]]-[[9th millennium BC]] of the [[Caspian Lowland]] (by [[Caspian Sea]]), from [[Ural River]] to [[Kuma-Manych Depression]]. It was discovered during the archaeological excavations near the Seroglazovka (Сероглазовка) ''[[stanitsa]]'' ([[Cossack]] settlement).

